Rating: 3
Fantastic! I, as always, made a few changes. First, I marinated the peeled shrimp in old bay seasoning & extra garlic powder. Then I sauteed minced garlic, chopped onion, dried thyme & rosemary in a tbsp or two of butter. I then added a bottle of beer and the shrimp shells and let it simmer. Seperately, in a very hot pan, I cooked the shrimp in another tbsp of butter until they were nice & crisp on the outside but still moist on the inside, adding another tbsp of butter at the end (note: there was some serious smoke in my small apartment kitchen). Then I removed the shells from the broth and added the broth to the shrimp/pan making sure to scrape up the brown bits in the pan. I know this version is different than the original recipe, but to be fair I made it as is first and liked this version better.

